  --tg-btn-padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem;
  --tg-btn-radius: 6px;
}


Remove Output Border
[data-toggle-output] {
  border-top: none;
}

Dark Mode
The extension adapts automatically via prefers-color-scheme and Quarto’s theme classes. Quarto adds .quarto-dark to the body in dark mode and .quarto-light in light mode.
To customize dark mode colors:
/* For Quarto's theme switcher (class on body) */
.quarto-dark {
  --tg-btn-bg: #2a2a2a;
  --tg-btn-bg-hover: #3a3a3a;
  --tg-btn-border: #555;
  --tg-btn-text: #e0e0e0;
}

/* For system preference (when not using Quarto themes) */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  :root {
    --tg-btn-bg: #2a2a2a;
    --tg-btn-bg-hover: #3a3a3a;
    --tg-btn-border: #555;
    --tg-btn-text: #e0e0e0;
  }
}

Adding Custom CSS
Reference a CSS file in your document:
format:
  html:
    css: custom.css
Or use inline styles:
&lt;style&gt;
:root {
  --tg-btn-bg: #your-color;
}
&lt;/style&gt;

How do I customize the appearance?
Override CSS custom properties using the --tg-* prefix:
:root {
  /* Button colors */
  --tg-btn-bg: #f0f0f0;
  --tg-btn-bg-hover: #e0e0e0;
  --tg-btn-border: #ccc;
  --tg-btn-text: #333;

  /* Button sizing */
  --tg-btn-radius: 3px;
  --tg-btn-font-size: 0.8rem;
  --tg-btn-padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;

  /* Other options */
  --tg-sync-indicator: #0066cc;
  --tg-focus-color: #0066cc;
  --tg-output-border-color: #ccc;
  --tg-output-border-style: dashed;
}
The extension uses Bootstrap variables as fallbacks when available. See the Custom Styling guide for full details.

Why does my button overlap with the copy button?
The extension adjusts automatically. If you still see overlap, add custom CSS:
.code-toggle-btn {
  right: 6rem;
}

